ith 2,107 missing and 401 confirmed captured between 5 July and 16 September 1950. In addition, the lives of tens of thousands of South Korean soldiers and civilians were lost as well.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199056-187\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199056_187-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFStokesbury1990\">Stokesbury 1990</a>, p.&#160;56.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEBarnouinYu2006141-188\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBarnouinYu2006141_188-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFBarnouinYu2006\">Barnouin &amp; Yu 2006</a>, p.&#160;141.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199047–48,_66-189\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199047–48,_66_189-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFStokesbury1990\">Stokesbury 1990</a>, pp.&#160;47–48, 66.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199058-190\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEStokesbury199058_190-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFStokesbury1990\">Stokesbury 1990</a>, p.&#160;58.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-191\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-191\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1950v07/pg_793\">493rd meeting of the UN Security Council, 31 August 1950</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20160302173851/https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1950v07/pg_793\">Archived</a> 2 March 2016 at the <a href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a> <i><a href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_Security_Council\" title=\"Uni