orean+War\" class=\"Z3988\"></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ho1993-305\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ho1993_305-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r999302996\"/><cite id=\"CITEREFHo1993\" class=\"citation book cs1\">Ho, Jong Ho (1993). <i>The US Imperialists started the Korean War</i>. Pyongyang, N. Korea: Foreign Languages Publishing House. p.&#160;230. <a href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASIN_(identifier)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ASIN (identifier)\">ASIN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0000CP2AZ\">B0000CP2AZ</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+US+Imperialists+started+the+Korean+War&amp;rft.place=Pyongyang%2C+N.+Korea&amp;rft.pages=230&amp;rft.pub=Foreign+Languages+Publishing+House&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0000CP2AZ%23id-name%3DASIN&amp;rft.aulast=Ho&amp;rft.aufirst=Jong+Ho&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKorean+War\" class=\"Z3988\"></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-KCNA2011-306\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-KCNA2011_306-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r999302996\"/><cite class=\"citation web cs1\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120529130625/http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2011/201108/news01/20110801-02ee.html\">\"War Victory Day of DPRK Marked in Different Countries\"</a>. KCNA. 1 August 2011. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kcna.co.jp/item/2011/201108/news01/20110801-02ee.html\">the original</a> on 29 May 2012<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 December</span> 2011</span>.</cite><s