 Union), and <a href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Sixth_Fleet\" title=\"United States Sixth Fleet\">Sixth Fleet</a> deployments in the Mediterranean left only the under-strength <a href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/4th_Marine_Division_(United_States)\" title=\"4th Marine Division (United States)\">4th Marine Division</a>&#160;– a reserve unit&#160;– available for combat in the western Pacific.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Shipmate2000-346\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Shipmate2000_346-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r999302996\"/><cite id=\"CITEREFKrulak,_Lieutenant_General_Victor_H.,_USMC,_retired2000\" class=\"citation journal cs1\">Krulak, Lieutenant General Victor H., USMC, retired (June 2000). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20021113195108/http://www.usna.com/News_pubs/Publications/Shipmate/2000/2000_06/inchon.htm\">\"You Can't Get There From Here: The Inchon Story\"</a>. <i>Shipmate</i>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.usna.com/News_pubs/Publications/Shipmate/2000/2000_06/inchon.htm\">the original</a> <span class=\"cs1-format\">(– <sup><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?q=intitle%3AYou+Can%27t+Get+There+From+Here%3A+The+Inchon+Story&amp;as_publication=Shipmate&amp;as_ylo=2000&amp;as_yhi=2000&amp;btnG=Search\">Scholar search</a></sup>)</span> on 13 November 2002.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Shipmate&amp;rft.atitle=You+Can%27t+Get+There+From+Here%3A+The+Inchon+Story&amp;rft.date=2000-06&amp;rft.au=Krulak%2C+Lieutenant+General+Victor+H.%2C+USMC%2C+retired&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.usna.com%2FNews_pubs%2FPublications%2FShipmate%2F2000%2F2000_06%2Finchon.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wik